==English==

===Etymology===
Probably a play on the pattern of words like [[fractious]]

===Adjective===
'''bumptious'''
# [[obtrusive]]ly [[pushy]]; [[self-assertive]] to a [[pretentious]] [[extreme]]
#: ''the politician may have had good ideas, but he was '''bumptious''' to a fault''

===Quotations===
#*'''1928''', [[w:Virginia Woolf|Virginia Woolf]], ''[[w:Orlando:_A_Biography|Orlando]]''
#*: She could [[stand]] it no longer. It was full of [[pry|prying]] old women, she said, who stared in one's face, and of '''bumptious''' young men who [[trod]] on one's toes.

